    "body": "You could work around this with a custom rendering that calls `searchForItems` any time there's a query and it renders. It won't do extra requests as it's already done and cached. Would this workaround work for you?\r\n\r\nWe've considered fixing this in the past but the use case didn't come up often and considered an edge case for now.",
